    <section id="tracks">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head">
          <p class="eyebrow">Program tracks</p>
          <h2>Three connected ways to grow.</h2>
          <p>Each track supports the same local canopy plan, so residents, volunteers, and partners can join at the level that fits them best.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cards">
          <article class="card">
            <p class="kicker">Home grove</p>
            <h3>Start small at home</h3>
            <p>Residents begin with a simple tree-planting pilot, building confidence and adding shade, habitat, and beauty one yard at a time.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <p class="kicker">Neighborhood canopy</p>
            <h3>Plant where it helps most</h3>
            <p>Community sites, low-canopy blocks, and shared spaces become planting priorities supported by volunteers and local sponsors.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <p class="kicker">Long-term care</p>
            <h3>Keep trees alive and thriving</h3>
            <p>Watering, mulching, stewardship walks, and check-ins turn planting day into a real survival plan.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="actions">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head">
          <p class="eyebrow">How it works</p>
          <h2>A simple shared action plan.</h2>
          <p>Instead of separate tree projects, this page organizes work into one local flow that people can follow and support together.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="timeline">
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-num">1</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Identify sites</h3>
              <p>Map home yards, church grounds, schools, and public-facing spaces that can host visible pilot trees.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-num">2</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Launch pilots</h3>
              <p>Start with a small group of households and one or two neighborhood planting locations to show momentum early.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-num">3</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Build stewardship</h3>
              <p>Create simple watering schedules, mulching days, and seasonal check-ins so maintenance is shared and visible.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="step">
            <div class="step-num">4</div>
            <div>
              <h3>Grow partnerships</h3>
              <p>Invite neighborhood groups, schools, local leaders, and donors into one network instead of separate campaigns.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="support">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head">
          <p class="eyebrow">Support structure</p>
          <h2>More than planting day.</h2>
          <p>Healthy canopy growth needs education, stewardship, partnerships, and funding that lasts beyond the first shovel in the ground.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="cards">
          <article class="card">
            <p class="kicker">Education</p>
            <h3>Teach the why</h3>
            <p>Neighborhood talks, school learning, and simple tree-care guides help residents connect climate, shade, and community health.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <p class="kicker">Workforce</p>
            <h3>Train local stewards</h3>
            <p>Youth crews, seasonal stipends, or volunteer captains can support planting, watering, and long-term tree care.</p>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <p class="kicker">Partnerships</p>
            <h3>Share responsibility</h3>
            <p>Churches, schools, nonprofits, and city partners can provide sites, volunteers, tools, and outreach.</p>
          </article>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section>
      <div class="container">
        <div class="section-head">
          <p class="eyebrow">Giving levels</p>
          <h2>Simple ways to fund the work.</h2>
          <p>A tiered ladder gives neighbors and sponsors an easy way to support trees, care, education, and larger planting days.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="donation-grid">
          <div class="donation-item"><span>$125 — One tree</span><span>Helps plant a tree where canopy is needed.</span></div>
          <div class="donation-item"><span>$500 — Care package</span><span>Supports watering and maintenance for young trees.</span></div>
          <div class="donation-item"><span>$2,500 — Learning support</span><span>Helps fund tree education and community outreach.</span></div>
          <div class="donation-item"><span>$5,000+ — Stewardship lead</span><span>Supports youth leadership, crews, or a major planting day.</span></div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section id="join">
      <div class="container">
        <div class="cta">
          <p class="eyebrow">Join the network</p>
          <h2>Pick your way in.</h2>
          <p>You can help by planting at home, volunteering for a neighborhood project, offering a site, or backing the work as a donor or partner.</p>
          <div class="hero-actions">
            <a class="button button-primary" href="mailto:hello@example.org">Contact the organizer</a>
